<user_id>107810543513567801709</user_id><user_name>Christopher Smith</user_name><date>1576851920757</date><rating>5<//rating>< Text>
Update: The everyday drink special keeps me coming back. Large beer and large hot sake 7.95. New menu just came out which lowered some prices and added items. The rest still applies. Stopped in for lunch and sat at the bar. They always give you a nice greeting. I've had the scallops rolls which have Amazing flavor and texture. It's cool watching the chefs prepare dishes right in front of you. They are friendly and answered all my questions. Clean with great family friendly service. I notice a lot of regular customers keep coming back. I highly recommend you try it.</Text>

<Review>Never going again.
My family goes here because it's local. Mom and pop place, we like to promote small business. We LOVE sushi.
My husband likes to sit at the bar and watch, and will chat with the chef.
The last couple times we've gone, the chef has commented on my weight.
This time, he explained no one should need more than one roll to be full.
We usually order several rolls, then we all share. My husband stopped eating as soon as the discussion started. He is sensitive about his weight even though he is not heavy. He asked for his second roll to be boxed. My daughter doesn't have a weight problem, and loves sushi. Going out is a special treat. She asked that her second roll be boxed. I tried to salvage the experience for my family by telling them the sushi would be good for lunch tomorrow, etc.
I wanted to try the pan fried noodle, and was encouraging the others to try it.  When I was able to sample it, even after eating a roll, the chef laughed at me, shaking his head in disbelief. I had the rest of the dish boxed.

We aren't going back.
Eating out is supposed to be a relaxing and fun experience, not one where you are being judged and openly ridiculed by the person to whom you are handing your money.< /Review>< name>
Diu Truly<//name>

< text>
Okay, this company is Definitely going to be around for the long haul as they are competitively priced, making them an great option for carpet cleaning services.l, which I like and their staff is friendly.
I must admit I was skeptical to use them at first considering that I saw their special on Groupon.But I promise you will not be disappointed as long as you call them and ask them exactly what it is that you are going to get.
Also expect an upsell from the technician once he visits your home, telling you that you need some extra stuff in addition to what you purchased,  so be prepared for that  but if you stick to your guns you will be fine and let them know you just want the service that  you ordered.

The carpets were steam cleaned, They looked pretty nice when they were dried as It was hard to tell the difference while they were still wet. I left my AC on and gave it a few hours to dry and I'm happy with the results.

I ended up getting the deodorizer which I won't recommend paying for because they claim to scent last for a month  but once the floor dried it disappeared. If you're going to pay for that just make sure you may regret it l depending on what it costs.

I will definitely use these guys again as their customer service was pretty solid and their response time is pretty great also.

My advice,  keep up the great work and throw in  the  deodorizer  for free It's definitely not an upsell< /text>

<UserId.>110028033851798198223<//UserId.><username>B Gutz< /username>< Date>
1465314066504<//Date>
<rating>3</rating>< Review>
I called to ask about the groupon before I purchased it to clarify exactly what I needed. Since I have a two-story house I had to buy the two-story groupon even though the carpet is only on one story. It obviously costs more yet it doesn't include cleaning the carpet on the stairs. Stairs are extra. I was told by Eco Clean that groupon doesn't allow them to include the price of the stairs in the offer. I thought it was odd but was told it's only $3 per stair and they don't charge more for risers like other companies. I was also offered other services at a lower rate (tile and upholstery cleaning) since I was purchasing the groupon, and was told the price offered would be entered in my profile for the cleaner to see and honor.

Once the cleaner arrived I mentioned I purchased a groupon and was adding tile cleaning and upholstery cleaning. He wouldn't offer the same price on the tile cleaning because I wanted my kitchen counter tile cleaned and they only do floor tile. He said he would still do it if I wanted but not for that low of a price. I feel the lady who offered me this extra service should have clarified, or the cleaner should have honored the price. Then he proceeded to up sell me on carpet and upholstery cleaning.

I despise up selling! I would much rather use a company that is totally upfront about pricing even if I'm paying a little more for it. I bought a groupon for what seemed to be a decent price but found out from experience that the company's goal is to up sell once they are in your home; so much so that I even asked what I purchased the groupon for. Found out it was just for a basic shampooing. I suspect that the groupon price is no savings at all, probably close to the same price every other company offers so it looks good on paper but then once they're in your house you feel the need to purchase one of the other packages in addition or you're just wasting your money otherwise.

The cleaner was friendly. He called to let me know when he would be to my house and called again when he realized he would be a little late. He seemed experienced and knowledgeable. I paid after with a credit card and a tip option pops up at signing which is awkward especially after all the up selling at the beginning. Then the cleaner handed me his phone and said I just needed to fill out one more thing. Turns out it was a review. He didn't ask but just said it would take me two minutes to complete at the most. Since he was standing right there I almost filled out a good review for him because it was awkward not to otherwise. I didn't feel right about that because I read reviews beforehand and really rely on other people's experiences and I wasn't completely satisfied after my own. I asked if I could fill out the survey later once I have a chance to at least see how his work turns out. He tried to pressure me to fill it out right then so I simply declined. If the company insists on such a quick review I wonder how many of those reviews can really be trusted?

The job was done and seems to be fairly satisfactory. I think the carpets turned out well. I'm just a little disappointed because I don't like the way Eco Clean operates as a business. I will likely try someone else next time and see how the experience compares. In the meantime, I won't be recommending Eco Clean to my friends and family.< /Review>

< Review>
Was looking for something different for my Mom's visit.  My son suggested 3rd and U.  Sure why not?  It was excellent!  Wasn't feeling a beer so we had ciders!  So good!  Great burgers!  I tried the mushroom swiss and had them add grilled onions.   It was so good, burger was cooked perfectly and the bun was soft and did not overwhelm the meat!  But strange to say, the chipotle mayo was the star of the show.  I got it on a whim and everyone at the table ended up asking for their own. Can't wait to go back, it may be our new go to burger joint.< /Review>

Fraudulent business. I was on my way up to big bear when I was stopped and told I needed chains. I asked around where I could get some and was told to try Mountain High market. There was only one employee working whom I found out later was new. I‚Äôve never had any experience with chains until this day, so I asked the employee if it was better to have 4 chains or two for my front wheel drive sedan. She said 4 would be better so I asked to buy 4. I placed my phone displaying a photo of my tire and tire size on the booklet and the employee helped me find my chain size, or so I thought. She went to the back room and came back with a bag of chains. She explained the no refund policy and I bought the chains with my debit card. When I opened the bag, I found two chains instead of the four I had requested. Additionally, they weren‚Äôt the right size. They were unusable, not even close to fitting. I asked the lady to return them and she refused, stating there were no refunds. I told her, ‚ÄúI understand the policy but you sold me the incorrect item. I asked for four chains and you sold me two that don‚Äôt fit my car. If you don‚Äôt accept the return this is fraud.‚Äù She called her manager, Kelly, who instructed her not to complete the refund. I decided to try to go up the mountain anyhow and had a great day of skiing (apparently the chains didn‚Äôt need to be on my car, I had to have them with me just in case). On my way back down I decided to stop by Mountain High in hopes a manager or different employee with better morals might be there. A different employee was there, and I told her I was sold the wrong item and it would be fraudulent if they didn‚Äôt honor the return. She called Kelly again, and Kelly told her to not honor the refund. I asked to speak to Kelly and was refused, so I told them I was calling the police. The police showed up and I made a police report. I left my chains on the counter and left. I filed a fraud report with my credit card company who finished the investigation and reimbursed me today with the 140$ I spent on a single pair of chains. Chains cost 50$ at Walmart. This shop is committing highway robbery on the regular and is fraudulent in its business practices. DO NOT BUY FROM MOUNTAIN HIGH MARKET. Do not support a business that scams its customers. Kelly is scum of the earth ordering her employees to commit fraud on her behalf. Do not support this illegal establishment. whatsoever.</review>

< review>
This Starbucks is located inside the Wells Fargo building which happens to be the oldest building in the city. The building is gorgeous and all you need to do is look up and you will instantly find peace. There are plenty of tables and couches to lounge on while you sip on your caffeine. For all you budding novelists and screenplay writers, this is the ideal coffee shop to plug in and type away. Starbucks inconveniently shares their restroom with Wells Fargo so you need to enter the bank area if you need to go.<//review>

<Review>What's not to like about rich, creamy and flavorful ice cream, decadent sundaes and great variety of hot and cold sandwiches and salads, all in a setting of a retro Ice Cream  Parlour that has served generations of guests. A great selection of ice cream, sorbets and toppings. An awesome place for celebratory groups and families. The crab sandwich on toasted French bread and the Roast Beef with Au jus are two long time favorites of mine that come with tasty fries with great texture or side salad. <userid>102207001333337646374< /userid>< Review>
One of the best, if not the best, ice cream shop and restaurant in the Bay Area. Not only is this place featured in the Pixar animated film Up but it defiantly lives up to the endorsement. The dinner and lunch food is tasty, not the best, but the ice cream, oh my goodness they do this well! All the ice cream is made in house, and is of the highest standard. If you get even a small scoop it will be more then worth your time. I love getting the Black and White with marshmallow on top. Only down side is the side is the parking lot is tiny. I usually park on the street and walk a block or two.
Going back for my birthday and a few friends, never regret it!</Review>

< Name>
Michael Manguinao<//Name>
<time>1496674225214<//time><rating>5<//rating><review>Perfect for all your all-day or late-night sweet tooth cravings! Great for group outings and celebrations. You definitely get that family-owned feel.

Just want a scoop (or why not two) of your favorite flavor? Don't be intimidated by the perpetually long line pouring out of the front double doors. The uber-friendly staff keeps the line moving fast and people going in and out quickly with their decadent desires?

Or maybe you want something to eat or a more adventurous treat? You and your group can take a seat and order from a variety of parlor foods and treats, from classic burgers to shakes and pies. Of course, the main attractions are the MASSIVE sundaes that Fenton's is famous for. My friends and I were feeling quite adventurous and celebratory (it was one of their birthdays), so we split a Banana Special, the featured sundae on the menu. When they say "three HUGE scoops of ice cream", it's really an understatement. What we got looked more like three whole pints really, all over a sweet, ripe banana and topped off with strawberry jam, chocolate, pineapple, whipped cream, and a cherry. It was outright delicious and filling, and I'm sure glad we had a team to finish it.</review>< pictures>

<review>Have come here few times for ice cream and couple times to eat a bite!

Food is 3.5 stars, old school burgers, sandwiches and other items are pretty decent. Ice cream is quite nice although i only like few choices that are light otherwise most of the stuff is pretty heavy, though it's homemade style so all good ;) Old time favorite is the junior size black tan sundae and the petite size scoop of caramel crunch :)

Place is usually busy no matter the season with enough indoor seating and few seats outside with a cute little fountain. Bathrooms are neat and clean most of the time.

Service is quick and super friendly :)<//review><Pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPpcC4fzqudkPEKdkQD824WLIm5DHiCUoN8AHSj=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPZauki6VD8kuMmBbIqCYdcFHYlUwMISdeJkC0v=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNFVD__SimT9XsuuziQLpK-PGooseVdcgbkRlPw=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPyJox3RMCE7SpLf_Tek6HNImeVBkuyYVWBDcvV=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPQUmauVZmPBab7ZD2wZjSohBlKqUHZvY2u1Z5x=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPdaAHJkiJ4yZO_yAZ5IWf-gw_8eBT9Fp4nMm1h=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipP6V7t2DjnMZ4ZnPT-JHKUnIiwlVG-7ZcpFsasj=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOv0graqgWL7j0mNsWd889gRaQRy8nihQceca8m=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//Pics>< resp>

<Text>Good : A great family resturant. Very american style food that is always delicious. The menu has healthier and les healthy options to cater to all. Fentons has a nice feel of an old ice cream parlor. A perfect spot for a child's birthday party as they do sing and give an ice cream treat.
Also was featured in the Pixar movie "up", which is a fun fact!

Bad: Acoustics are bad and it gets very loud inside, so not a great place to have a first date or chat with family or friends. Also the tables are very small and cramped (especially in groups of four). Usually pretty crowded. Parking is also difficult to find so expect to walk a bit.< /Text>< pictures>

<user_name>Miriam Smith<//user_name><review>First time here. Wow! Waited 25 minutes for a table, which wasn't too bad for a Sunday afternoon. Dining area is loud; don't come for the ambiance, lol. Ordered turkey bacon melt with onion rings. Melt was delicious, the grilled turkey and salty bacon mellowed by the swiss cheese. Onion rings were crispy and flavorful. Not sure what they dredge it in, but it's tasty.
Ordered a Black & White Junior which, surprisingly, wasn't as sweet or rich as I thought it'd be. The vanilla ice cream was smooth and tempered the richness of the chocolate ice cream. The marshmallow and fudge were balanced with the whipped cream. I probably should've ordered the regular size.
Hostess was friendly. Staff was helpful and checked my table often.

Two things to keep in mind:
1. The parking lot is extremely small for such a well-known and busy establishment. Be prepared to park somewhere along Piedmont and walk.
2. This is not an inexpensive eatery. Be prepared to drop bills. I was part of a party of four. Our bill topped out just over $100 before tax and tip. But it was worth it, if just for the privilege to say, "I've eaten there."</review><UserId.>113091130672951483434</UserId.></record>

<Time>1579980356407<//Time>< text>
I was in this area for an appointment and had some time to spare so decided I should stop here for an ice cream cone.  First happy thing was that they have a parking lot so no need to search.  Then I perused their list of flavors and decided on Pistachio.  Although I had a cone I decided to take a spoon to help me along.  When I put that first spoonful in my mouth I could not believe the taste.  It was fabulous!  It was remarkably creamy, had lots of pistachio nuts and the flavor was like nothing I have ever had before.  It might have had touches of almond or lemon along with the pistachio.  Whatever it was, I loved it!  I don't think I had ever been here before but, if so, it was over 30 years ago.  I have to have a return visit now!<//text>

< Name>
Ed Ditlefsen< /Name>
<Time>1490306478610</Time><Rating>5</Rating>< Review>
Great food, great ice cream, great ambiance, great service. Order the Sundae of the Month and be prepared to receive a bowl of ice cream as big as your head.

Two logistical items to note when planning your visit to Fentons: 1) When they get busy (which is almost all the time), they won't seat you until all members of your party are there. 2) Finding parking can be extremely difficult.

If you're looking for t-shirts and other souvenirs, visit  "Myrtle's Lodge", Fentons' official gift shop, across the street.< /Review>

< text>
If you like LARGE portions of ice cream...COME HERE. The prices have gone up quite a bit. I grew up near here, would go here often. When I was home visiting one time, my mom told me some shocking news...FENTONS IS CLOSED????? What???? This can't be??? If any of you remember when a fire happened here.

I do remember one time when I went here and with one of the servers here at the time. The service was TERRIBLE...that was then, this is now.
Fenton's is like the Six Million Dollar Man...we can rebuild Fenton's..updated, cleaner, and still THE BEST ice cream.

I can remember when the BIG sundaes were $5.00 a pop, now the sundaes are $15.00 a pop. Fenton's still rules.  And thanks to the movie UP for making this place famous.<//text>

<Text>This is a favorite and has been all my life.  My parents even went on dates here.  While I miss the old yellowish coloring that seemed to cover the inside years ago, it is a very clean somewhat timeless look with a few key elements like the candy drop shape of the lights and the wire chairs that still remind me of the past.  The ice cream as always was huge and delicious.  Prices for a huge sundae are not cheap but it is a treat and not something to do all of the time.  We were very lucky and found parking in the lot which only holds about 7 or 8 cars.  We also were lucky on timing because we only had to wait about 15 minutes for a table to seat 4.  This is a landmark for the East Bay Area and has been immortalized in the movie "Up".  If you are in the area and enjoy a really great sundae with excellent ice cream, you really should try to visit Fentons.<//Text><user_name>Brad Hunter<//user_name><rate>5< /rate>< response>

<Rating>4<//Rating><Review>There's two different ways to do Fentons.

Option 1 - to go. The right side when you enter is where you'll line up, try a couple of different flavors and then decide what flavor you want and head out. Maybe sit outside on one of their benches or tables. Or walk along Piedmont Ave.

Option 2 - sit down. Their menu has not only various desserts like banana splits and sundaes but also diner food like sandwiches and fries. It's got that old-school diner feel. The service is okay but also just a nice place to catch up and grab dessert.<//Review><pictures>None</pictures><Resp>None< /Resp>< Gmap_id>

Favorite spot to celebrate a special occasion or to treat friends! Friendly staff and good food, including their salads, but it can be hard to hold conversations during peak hours since this place can get busy. Of course, you can just stop by to get a cone or cup of ice cream, made on site and wide selection of flavors (toasted almond my fav). Parking can also be tough to find during dinner hours.< /text>

<user>101826043610087762327< /user><name>Ellena Mar< /name>< date>
1582472560084</date>
< rating>
5<//rating>
<Text>Great food AND amazing ice cream - how much better can it get!  Well, if there was a parking garage nearby that would help but I will gladly brave traffic and the parking gods any day to go to Fenton's.  I've been going to this original location for 20+ years and it still is unbelievable.   The ice cream is made in house and during the day you can actually watch the process thanks to the giant windows they have now in front of the area.  My favorite is the coffee ice cream with hot caramel.  I don't even drink coffee and this is my favorite flavor at Fenton's!  But I think that hot caramel on just about anything is super tasty.  For the savory side you have American diner fare but super fresh and surprisingly (well to me, at first) crave worthy.  Anything they have is delicious: fried food, salads, burgers, sandwiches, everything!  Must go if you are in the area or not.  It's an institution and immortalized in Pixar's Up though on the most recent visit - don't know where Doug the dog went.</Text>< Pics>
None</Pics>

< Text>
One of my friends invited me to come here for the first time and I thought it was similar to other ice cream places in the area where you just wait in line to get ice cream and then go. I was pleasantly surprised to find out that they have a diner and you can order normal food and then get a dessert afterwards.

The dessert menu is vast and they have some local favorites that are really nice. They are also humongous and I didn't know this so my friend and I both ordered a dessert to share and it was massive. Even after working on just a dessert both had to get packed up and taken away. It was part of the fun trying to figure out how to stuff our faces with ice cream.</Text>

<review>I ordered an ice cream cake on the phone on 6/8, and when I went to pick it up on 6/22, they had the order but not the cake! I checked my call history and confirmed they'd never called.

The manager was kind and offered a gift certificate for next time, but I declined because I don't think I'll be back.

I can't figure out what happened, but it seems likely that they got my phone number wrong when I ordered over the phone (even though they read it back to me). Maybe the person trying to call couldn't read the handwriting of the person who took the order. Seems like it'd be worth the extra trouble to make sure this doesn't happen when you only support ordering over the phone (and by fax, which... seriously?) Online ordering would have prevented this.

Really wish this had worked out; their cakes look great! But I was counting on them and they let me down. If you're going to give them a try, call them a second time a couple days before you plan to pick up!<//review><pictures>None</pictures>< Resp>

< Text>
Fenton's should get 5 stars but I only gave it 4. The place is extremely noisy and it is not a place where you go to have a business meeting.
They get so busy that they forget your food orders. We ordered a french dip sandwich that came after the banana split. We had to remind the server we were still waiting for our food. It was like forever.
I understand you go to Fenton's for ice cream but no one should have the dessert before the main meal.
Prices have gone up and the portions are huge but beware of a sugar rush.
You're better off getting a cone in the take out line.</Text>

< date>
1424287800091<//date>
< Rate>
4< /Rate>
<Review>Great ice cream options. You can't really go wrong with any flavor they have.

When you get there will be a line out the door. Don't get discouraged. This place doesn't have a really good way to queue up the people waiting to get a scoop. Just find parking and then get in line. It moves pretty quickly.

If you're getting ice cream only (not eating in) there won't be a ton of options to sit and lounge. You may need to walk around or get back in the car and leave.

The food here is just really basic and average. But they make it up with the ice cream. The prices for everything is what you'd expect; nothing too high and nothing too low.<//Review><pictures>None< /pictures>< Resp>
None</Resp>

<time>1522390834923<//time><rate>5<//rate>< text>
Can't go wrong with a Fenton's sundae. I've tried burgers and the crab sandwich here and I like them both. If you're looking for something light to eat, the crab sandwich is good. Otherwise go for a burger. There's lots of different permutations that you can try. In addition to that, there's all the regular American diner fare: fries, milkshakes, chili dogs, etc. At the end of your meal you should definitely get a sundae.</text>

< username>

<date>1555636956204<//date><rating>4</rating>< text>
The service was great, our waiter was professional & kind, so was all the other wait staff we encountered...I willingly paid over $8 for a milkshake.  It was only ok, just not $8 good.  We ordered a basket of onion rings & the waiter brought us a metric ton of onion rings...the order of onion rings was $6.75.

My kids each got a kids ice cream cone, they both were more than the order of onion rings.

In fact all the non-ice cream menu items were the only reasonably priced items on the menu.

It was a nice place & obviously very popular but I couldn't figure out what justification there was to price their ice cream items so high.  It would be hard to come back knowing I could get the same caliber of ice cream for half the price anywhere else.<//text>

< date>
1490579231875<//date>
< Rating>
5</Rating>
<Text>A local ice cream joint in a hip neighborhood in Oakland. The place is spacious with outdoor sitting, complete with fountains. There are plenty of seatings inside as well. Service was quick and painless to get your ice cream. Their scoops are huge, and I really suggest to just get petite size. It will be more than enough, trust me.

The ice cream was good, but not that mind blowing good. It's still better than most ice cream places I've been to though. I'd say don't make special trip here, but when you're in the area to do other things, do swing by and get some ice cream here. Maybe even sit outside by the fountain when the weather permits. Definitely a good experience.<//Text>< Pics>

<userid>116018211746666534134</userid><Pictures>None< /Pictures>< review>
The shiz. You can't ask for a larger "small" size of ice cream. This place is destined to make the world fat and I'm ok with that. One scoop at a time is what I keep telling myself.

Fenton's is your classic diner with good food and better ice cream. Get here and expect a little wait, even if it's just for the 'cream because this place packs up quick. Flavors are simple yet amazing and the best thing you can do for yourself is indulge! Get a sundae on a Sunday and plan to stay awhile because even the truest ice cream aficionados couldn't eat this 'cream quick.

If you've got kids take them on an ice cream tour - yes they do that here.</review>

<userid>104987932455782713675< /userid><Text>The ice cream here is the best in the Bay Area.  My favorite is the toasted almond.  They make great sundaes that are big and generous and can be shared with the whole family.  Sharing one big sundae is much more economical than getting the kids each their own cones.  Child cones are expensive (I think live $5 each) but I'll take my family of 4 kids there and we'll share a sundae for $10 instead.

As good as the ice cream is, I'm not a fan of their other food.  It's pretty basic burgers and fries type stuff and overpriced and not very good.  I gave it a 3 on food, but that rating was just for the ice cream.

Another good value is getting a prepacked half gallon to go.  They have a few flavors (fortunately one is toasted almond) that you can buy cheaper prepacked.  I think a prepacked half gallon is cheaper than a handpacked quart.

Sometimes we'll buy one of those and take it home and enjoy the ice cream and have more left over for the week.

When I've dined there the service has been poor.  More than once I've had to get up myself at my table to go pay my bill or to go get something that I need like napkins.  I think they have too few and too inexperienced servers working there covering too many tables.< /Text><date>1338556189827</date><Pics>None</Pics>< rating>

<Rate>5< /Rate><Review>Fenton's is the your classic ice cream shop. Their massive sundaes, made with a wide range of fun flavors and rich homemade toppings are the thing of legends, but they've also got a serviceable selection of sandwiches, burgers, and other diner-style fare if you need to start with something savory.

Pro tip: ask for "cold fudge" instead of hot fudge. It's actually room temperature, and will help to keep that gigantic creation from melting before you can eat it all (you were planning to eat it all, right?)< /Review><Pictures>None<//Pictures>< resp>

< Text>
It's sacrilege so say anything bad about Fentons but these days I just don't feel the ice cream is worth the wait and the noise. Perhaps I'm just getting more grouchy as the years pass (well, not perhaps it's true) but there are other ice cream places in the area, and other places to get diner type food.

Feeling better saying that I can say that the meals are average and the ice cream and ice cream concoctions are very good. If you're going to come try to come when it's not as busy so you don't have to wait too long for a seat or for your turn in line for a to-go treat.<//Text>

<rating>4<//rating><text>A staple for the area, and there's never a time to go when there won't be  line of excited people.

An old-school ice creamery, so there won't be any of those high falutin' flavors you're used to from Tara's, Bi-Rite, but Fentons knows how to do solid ice cream well. Toasted almond is delicious, but I always get the apple pie flavor when it's seasonally available (are apples ever NOT available?).

The ice cream all comes with little cookies, and even the tiniest size is a hefty wallop of dairy.

Food is decent as well, though come here for the sweet icy concoctions!</text><pics>None</pics><response>None</response>< gmapID>

< review>
Fenton delivers exactly what you came for! Large generous portions and amazing portions. It's a fun, family friendly atmosphere. It's diner style offering an array of great portions. I had the French Dip and it was exactly what I expected with no surprises. The foods great but the real star are the heaping desserts! I ordered the Cookie Connection. It's a warm chocolate chip cookie smothered with two large scoops of ice cream, cookie dough and cookies n' cream. Marshmallow sauce, chocolate fudge and crushed oreos! I could not even complete it but it was an amazing journey! Would definitely come again!<//review>

<pics>None< /pics>< Time>
1581488219946< /Time>
<Text>Toasted Almond ice cream is a must try!</Text></record></dataset><record>
<gmapID>0x80857df6c43cdebb:0x91f2ea4405beec30<//gmapID>< text>
It's an Easy Bay fixture with a lot of history although a lot of the old school character was lost during the fire years ago. But it's bigger brighter and louder now - about the only quiet time is early afternoon in the week when the kids are not around but at all other times expect to pick up a buzzer add wait. There is also a take out line for those wanting a quick fix. Bar seating is quicker too if you're okay with that. There is also a back room that can be rather chilly - you might actually believe you're in an  ice-cream factory.

Ice cream dessert portions are epically huge, i was once mocked for only ordering a junior sundae after dinner - but the thing was huge anyway. My advice - being a friend and your appetite!  Ice cream flavours include seasonal items, don't be shy about asking for a sample of you're unsure.< /text>

< Text>
We went to Fenton's on a Saturday night, as it was highly recommended by locals. We opted to sit outside and were seated right away, even though it was busy. (I guess most people wanted to sit inside.) Our waitress was attentive and kind, giving us extra info about the menu and her recommendations. We ordered dinner (burgers) and then got the saddleback brownie. My hubby's burger order got messed up, but they remade it and gave us half off his entree, which was above-and-beyond. The dessert was excellent (amazing brownie!), but after burgers, my stomach probably would've been better off with a simple scoop of ice cream! :) We'll be back to try some other desserts.< /Text>

<Name>Chuck McIntyre< /Name><date>1284781721098< /date><rate>4</rate>< review>
Fenton's is an ice cream place that also serves American Diner food. The ice cream is one of the best in the bay. The food is mediocre at best. There's also very little vegetarian friendliness.  They have veggie burgers but they're made on a shared grill, etc. The place is usually packed but waits aren't long. Parking can be tricky.<//review>

5< /Rating>
< text>
Who doesn't love Fenton's?! Parking is always hard, but it's worth it. Their selection of ice cream flavors is enormous, their portion sizes border on the ridiculous (a "single" scoop is actually a double), and their sundaes are infamously delicious. We take my stepson here every year for his birthday, and my husband and I go there to celebrate sometimes, too. The food is decent, but in the greasy diner food category. Everyone should visit Fenton's at least once for dessert. Or often :-)< /text>

<review>What's not to like about an ice cream parlor? I mean, at the very worst, it's still ice cream!

Occasionally, there's a bit of a wait, but that's just because other people like their ice cream too -- don't hold that against them.

My favorite thing to get is the Banana Special, because I have an inner fat kid who's just trying to get out. Remember when ordering large though: mix up those flavors. You don't want to get stuck with a bunch of the same.

That being said, ice cream is a go!<//review>< Rate>

<time>1433485989331</time><UserId.>110288469148184652948< /UserId.>< review>
Great burgers and sandwiches, and the best ice cream for dessert! Fenton's is an Oakland institution (did you catch it at the end of Pixar's Up?), famous for their ice cream made fresh on site. Be sure to put your name down with the hostess to get a seat. Fenton's is really accommodating and knows their customers well ("do i want fries or onion rings...?" Choose the half-and-half. Burgers and sandwiches are large and filling.

Their ice cream is worth the wait. Creamy and perfectly flavored, there's always something for everyone. The sundae us great to share with someone, but I personally like the black and tan. Their seasonal flavors are great too.

There is a small parking lot, but parking usually isn't too hard to find. Patio seating has heaters for the chilly nights, and there is a private back room for events.<//review>

< Rating>
5<//Rating>
<text>Our family goes to Fenton's a few times a year and we've never had bad food or ice cream, but we've sometimes had uneven service like long delays or mixed orders. Portions are unpredictable, with some sandwiches large and others small. Fenton's is always crowded and always noisy and the back room is best left to over-excited and over-sugared kids because you can't have a conversation back there. Parking in front is limited and requires luck. But if you're going to Fenton's you probably don't care about any of that. You're there for the delicious ice cream and photo-worthy giant sundaes. Fenton's is the Disneyland of ice cream and will have your kids wide-eyed in amazement and bouncing in their seats. They will talk about it for weeks and remember it forever. Like Disneyland, just be prepared to wait in line.</text>< response>
None</response>

<Name>Joe Goldstein<//Name>< Rate>
5</Rate>
< Time>
1484096523573</Time>
<pictures>None</pictures><text>There are two kinds of great ice cream parlors in the Bay Area. The first is artisanal, small batch parlors with inventive flavors and an absurd attention to detail, like The Ice Cream Bar in Haight or Bi-Rite Creamery. Fenton's is the other kind: their focus is on rich, classic flavors done right and stacked high, served in a busy but friendly atmosphere. The closest thing to it would be Leatherby's in Sacramento. There can be a decent wait during peak hours, and I haven't tried anything but their ice cream, but so far I wouldn't change a thing.< /text>< user>

<user>111785770370296789381<//user>< user_name>
Jay Hussein<//user_name>
<Date>1499418100543< /Date><rating>4<//rating><text>Right when I arrived to Fenton's, I already knew what was in store for me. The parking spot literally only had like five spaces and since there is hundreds of people inside. I decided not to wait unless I was trying to set a Guinness record of man that waited the longest for a parking spot. We had to drive and park one block away since there was many signs that warn we will tow you (your car) while you are enjoying Fenton's.

I wasn't too worried as it was a nice day for a walk. When we got to Fenton's, there were ten to fifteen people waiting. That day i got to know random people on a personal level accidentally since it was so crowded. There was only two of us so we got the stools right in front of the cooks ( I'm watching you cooks....).

The waitress came up and hurried us if we are ready yet. As it was our first time and we didn't even crack the menu we told her come back in a few mins.

We ended up ordering the jalapeno poppers tuna sandwich and cranberry turkey sandwich.
Jalapeno poppers were the BOMB! It was the right kind of crispy and soft in the inside.
The tuna sandwich was decent, nothing new or extraordinary here.
The cranberry turkey was great because the ingredients matched up perfectly and the savory cranberry oozing out the sandwich.
The superstar for this part was the curly fries. I don't recall that I have tasted a better curly fries than here! Crispy and soft as you bite into it making it hard to resist popping more in your mouth.

Now for my next act i would like to present the desert part!

We ordered the cookie crunch(not sure if real name) and the saddle back brownie sundaes. Sad to say is that we didn't know how big it really was.

The cookie crunch had two colossal scoops of ice cream. That rich cookie dough blended it with melting ice cream allied with cookies on the bottom! Every gushing flavor just twisting my mouth because of how bloody good it is! And that was only the first bite!

The saddle back brownie is a terrific name because that brownie is really the size of a saddle! Humungous! i'm talking about a entity that cannot be fully kept by the bowl! It came with two or three scoops of ice cream.The cold delicate ice cream paired with the hot brownie just told my taste buds into groupies awaiting its next arrival! As she just threw in the white surrender flag, I also waved my flag.

We ended taking more than half home. We went to town not too long after and just completely obliterated it.

If you will be going in there. Soldier give it a empty stomach because you will be going to war on those sundaes and I wish nothing but victory for you.</text>< pics>

< resp>
None</resp>
< text>
I'd heard about this place for a while but never checked it out till recently.  Wow what a surprise for a place that is so popular.  I guess you should stick with either the icecream or the burgers.  I can't believe how lousy our lunch was.  Sent back the fish and chips because the inside of the fish was frozen.  Then got the french dip which was soooo mediocre.  Eating it actually made feel kind of sick.  French dip is a hard one to screw up.  It appeared to be pre-sliced roast beef out of some package.  Understandable but low quality.  The bread was weirdly doughy and soft for a dutch crunch roll.  My wife's sandwich wasn't any better.  There were plenty of servers but they never filled our tiny dixie cup size water glass unless we asked them.  Also, had to ask for salt and pepper shakers to try and pull some flavor from my sandwich.  The servers all were young with this deer in the headlights kind of look.  I know they're not a deli and are know for their icecream and history but these $14 sandwiches  were really crappy.  I felt like I ate at McDonalds or something.  Not going back.</text>
